At the [[NFL Combine]], Graham ranked 8th among defensive linemen with a 4.72 [[40-yard dash]] and 10th in the [[bench press]] with 31.<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.nfl.com/combine/top-performers?tabIndex=0#tp-tab-set-1:tp-grid-container-forty-yard-dash|title=Results (40-yard dash) |work=NFL.com |accessdate=2010-04-24 }}.</ref><ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.nfl.com/combine/top-performers?tabIndex=0#tp-tab-set-1:tp-grid-container-bench-press|title=Results (bench Press) |work=NFL.com |accessdate=2010-04-24 }}.</ref>

===Philadelphia Eagles===
Graham was drafted by the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] 13th overall after trading up in the [[2010 NFL Draft]].  Graham decided to wear number 94 for the Eagles immediately after the draft,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/news/Story.asp?story_id=20949|title=Brandon Graham, Nate Allen Jersey Numbers|accessdate=2010-04-25|date=2010-04-23|publisher=[[Philadelphia Eagles]]|author=Wulf, Bo}}</ref> but changed his mind and chose number 54.<ref>{{cite web |author=McPherson, Chris |title=Roster Numbers For New Players |url=http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/news/Story.asp?story_id=21006 |publisher=''PhiladelphiaEagles.com'' |date=April 28, 2010 |accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref> Graham shares the same [[sports agent]] ([[Joel Segal (sports agent)|Joel Segal]]) as teammate [[Michael Vick]].<ref name=ORPGRTN/> He was the first [[Big Ten Conference]] player selected in the [[2010 NFL Draft]]. He agreed to terms on a five-year contract on July 29, 2010.<ref>{{cite news |author=Leahy, Sean |title=Philadelphia Eagles agree to deal with 13th overall pick Brandon Graham |url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/thehuddle/post/2010/07/philadelphia-eagles-agree-to-deal-with-13th-overall-pick-brandon-graham/1 |work=[[USA Today]] |date=July 29, 2010 |accessdate=2010-07-29}}</ref> Graham recorded his first NFL sack against the [[2010 Detroit Lions season|Detroit Lions]] in a week 2 win on September 19, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/nfl/boxscore?gameId=300919008|title=Eagles 35, (1-1, 1-0 away); Lions 32, (0-2, 0-1 home)|accessdate=2010-09-24|date=2010-09-19|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> After suffering a torn [[anterior cruciate ligament]] (ACL) in a week 14 game against the [[2010 Dallas Cowboys season|Dallas Cowboys]], Graham was placed on the [[injured reserve list]] on December 14.<ref>{{cite news |title=Source: Eagles to sign Derrick Burgess |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=5919557 |work=[[ESPN.com]] |date=December 14, 2010 |accessdate=2010-12-14}}</ref> He underwent [[microfracture surgery]] on his right knee on December 21.<ref>{{cite news |author=Meinke, Kyle |title=notebook: Brandon Graham expects to miss start of NFL season and more notes from Jalen Rose's golf outing |url=http://www.annarbor.com/sports/um-football/former-michigan-defensive-end-brandon-graham-expects-to-miss-beginning-of-nfl-season/ |work=annarbor.com |date=July 11, 2011 |accessdate=2011-07-20}}</ref> Graham was placed on the active/[[physically unable to perform]] list on July 28, 2011, before the start of training camp.<ref>{{cite news |author=McPherson, Chris |title=Graham, Justice Placed On PUP |url=http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/news/article-1/Graham-Justice-Placed-On-PUP/0bd2cceb-61de-45ed-b0d6-f3f587a3bbd2 |work=philadelphiaeagles.com |date=July 28, 2011 |accessdate=2011-07-28}}</ref> He was removed him from the physically unable to perform list so he could return to practice on October 24 and activated on November 5, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2011/11/05/eagles-activate-brandon-graham|title=Eagles activate Brandon Graham|accessdate=2011-11-06|date=2011-11-05|publisher=[[NBC Sports]]|author=Florio, Mike}}</ref>

